ia Kolbowski, Daniel Joseph Martinez, Lorna Simpson, Hans Haacke, Andrea Fraser and Charles Gaines. By turning to social issues, these artists analysed the conventions of language, photography, moving image, installation and display.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aArtxPolitical aspectsxUnited StatesxUnited States. 0aArtxPolitical aspectszUnited States. 0aConceptual artxUnited States. 0aConceptual artzUnited States. 0aConceptualism. 7aART / Conceptual.2bisacsh  aAdrian Piper.  aCharles Gaines.  aHans Haacke.  aJoseph Kosuth.  aWhitney Biennial.  acontemporaneous politics.  acontemporary art.  adisciplinary-based Conceptual Art.  aidentity politics.  ainterdisciplinary conceptualism.  aissue-based politics.  apolitical art.  apolitical reference.  asynthetic proposition artists.1 aShaked, Nizan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packagez978311128281740uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611941440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526119414423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526119414/original  a978-3-11-128281-7  Manchester University Press 2017 eBook-Packageb2017  aGBV-deGruyter-alles